# Ocelot API Gateway Example 

Ocelot is a .NET API Gateway used to unify microservices. 

this is a simple example showing how we can have 2 microservices ( CatalogAPI & OrdersAPI )
that can be called via the APIGateway

# Using the demo 

1 ) - Git clone this repositry 
2 ) - Dotnet restore the GatewayAPI, CatalogAPI & OrdersAPI 
2 ) - dotnet run CatalogAPI & OrdersAPI & GatewayAPI 

the two available endpoints are 

http://localhost:7000/orders-api/orders
http://localhost:7000/catalog-api/currency

The CatalogAPI runs on port 7001
The OrdersAPI runs on port 7002.